THE RISK:
{
 "id": "nl-grid-freeze-share-erosion",
 "title": "The Netherlands' 0.28 slice is legally and electrically frozen for the entire Year-1 window",
 "narrative": "geo.NL = 0.28 is one of the best-triangulated nodes in the ledger — Statista and the DDA agree within 3%. But both measure installed stock, and the venture sells into flow: new fit-outs where a new vendor can be designed in. In NL that flow is administratively shut for the whole first-12-months window: a national decree bans new hyperscale builds outside two municipalities, Amsterdam's draft zoning plan caps connections at 350 MVA until 2030, and distribution firms say no power is available until 2030 — with Amsterdam holding ~70% of national colo. What remains in NL is replacement demand inside operating halls, the most incumbent-locked business there is. Nearly a third of the funnel is a stock share masquerading as an addressable flow.",
 "category": "boundary",
 "targetNodes": [
  "geo.NL"
 ],
 "mechanism": [
  {
   "step": "trigger",
   "text": "National hyperscale ban outside Het Hogeland/Hollands Kroon, Amsterdam's 350 MVA connection ceiling to 2030, and grid operators reporting no power available until 2030",
   "refs": [
    "digest:geo-NL#c7",
    "digest:geo-NL#c8",
    "digest:geo-NL#c9"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "propagation",
   "text": "Amsterdam Metro holds ~70% of Dutch colo capacity, so the caps bind the bulk of the country; NL growth already decelerated to 4.9% CAGR 2021–23 — the flow of new fit-outs where a new PDU vendor gets specified approaches zero in the Year-1 window",
   "refs": [
    "digest:geo-NL#c12",
    "digest:geo-NL#c13"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "model-impact",
   "text": "NL's share of contestable Year-1 demand is far below its 0.28 installed-capacity share; the geography mix overweights a frozen market and inflates SAM and YAM proportionally",
   "refs": [
    "ledger:geo.NL"
   ]
  }
 ],
 "whyMissable": "The node is triangulated with two independent sources agreeing within ~3% — it looks like a solved cell. The failure mode is not measurement error but metric choice: installed MW is the wrong proxy for a new entrant's reachable demand in a market where new construction is banned and the grid is allocated to 2030.",
 "expectedObviousness": "medium",
 "falsifier": "Liander/Stedin announcing material new data-center grid allocations before 2030, or the DDA reporting >80 MW of newly commissioned Dutch colocation capacity within the venture's Year-1.",
 "likelihood": {
  "value": 0.5,
  "rationale": "The ban, the MVA cap and the grid unavailability statements are enacted or on the record for exactly this window; leakage exists via the Eemshaven/Agriport exception zones and private-substation workarounds like the Pure DC 78 MW campus, so the freeze is partial rather than total. [evidence revision: Regulatory freeze premises are firmly corroborated, but the DDA's record €1.4bn 2025 colo investment and explicit growth shift to Groningen/South Holland/North Brabant, plus Stedin freeing grid capacity for businesses in Zeeland, show meaningful new colo fit-out flow outside the Amsterdam cap. This weakens the 'flow approaches zero' step: the freeze is real but geographically narrower than the ~0.28 stock share implies, leaving the mechanism partial. Slight downward revision from 0.55 given documented ongoing national build activity, though the core Amsterdam/hyperscale binding holds.]",
  "basis": "evidence",
  "revisedFrom": 0.55
 },
 "perturbation": [
  {
   "nodeId": "geo.NL",
   "op": "set",
   "value": 0.2,
   "note": "Contestable NL slice shrinks in absolute terms (frozen new-build flow); deliberately not re-normalizing siblings — this is a smaller slice, not a mix shift"
  }
 ],
 "indicators": [
  {
   "signal": "Adoption status of Amsterdam's umbrella zoning plan and the 350 MVA connection ceiling",
   "where": "Gemeente Amsterdam planning docket and Dutch Data Center Association policy updates",
   "threshold": "Plan adopted with the 350 MVA cap intact",
   "updates": "increases"
  },
  {
   "signal": "National colocation capacity print year-on-year",
   "where": "DDA 'State of the Dutch Data Centers' annual report",
   "threshold": "National colo MW flat at ≤950 MW",
   "updates": "increases"
  }
 ],
 "mitigations": [
  {
   "action": "Obtain Liander/Stedin/TenneT NL connection-queue data for the data-center category to quantify how much NL fit-out actually proceeds through 2027",
   "type": "information",
   "voiNodeId": "geo.NL",
   "note": "Replaces the stock-based 0.28 with a flow-based reachable share"
  },
  {
   "action": "Concentrate NL go-to-market on the exception zones (Eemshaven, Agriport) and private-substation projects where new builds are still legal and powered",
   "type": "strategic",
   "voiNodeId": null,
   "note": null
  }
 ],
 "evidenceStatus": "contested",
 "evidence": [
  {
   "title": "Amsterdam | DC Byte",
   "sourceType": "industry-report",
   "publisher": "DC Byte",
   "date": "2025-01-19",
   "excerpt": "no new hyperscale data centres (<10 hectares/70+ MW) are allowed to be constructed in the Netherlands, except for a few locations in the municipalities of Het Hogeland and Hollands Kroon. Further regulation is planned for the Municipality of Amsterdam with a recent draft umbrella zoning plan suggesting that 350 MVA is the new maximum connection capacity within the municipality until 2030",
   "url": "https://www.dcbyte.com/market/amsterdam/",
   "attached": true
  },
  {
   "title": "Ten Years of State of the Dutch Data Centers",
   "sourceType": "industry-report",
   "publisher": "Dutch Data Center Association",
   "date": "2025-06-10",
   "excerpt": "In 2024, the total colocation capacity reached 924 megawatts. For 2025, the sector expects a record investment of more than €1.4 billion... While the Amsterdam Metropolitan Area (MRA) still accounts for approximately 70% of colocation capacity, growth is shifting toward regions such as Groningen, South Holland, and North Brabant",
   "url": "https://www.dutchdatacenters.nl/en/nieuws/ten-years-of-state-of-the-dutch-data-centers-a-decade-of-growth-and-challenges/",
   "attached": true
  },
  {
   "title": "Voorbeschermingsregels hyperscale datacentra (Staatscourant 2023, 35432)",
   "sourceType": "industry-report",
   "publisher": "Ministerie van Binnenlandse Zaken en Koninkrijksrelaties",
   "date": "2023-12-21",
   "excerpt": "deze instructieregels bepalen dat een omgevingsplan geen hyperscale datacentra toelaat",
   "url": "https://zoek.officielebekendmakingen.nl/stcrt-2023-35432.html",
   "attached": true
  }
 ],
 "stances": [
  {
   "url": "https://www.dcbyte.com/market/amsterdam/",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "since the start of 2024, an amended decree has meant that no new hyperscale data centres (<10 hectares/70+ MW) are allowed to be constructed in the Netherlands, except for a few locations in the municipalities of Het Hogeland (e.g. Eemshaven) and Hollands Kroon (e.g. Agriport). Further regulation is planned for the Municipality of Amsterdam with a recent draft umbrella zoning plan suggesting that 350 MVA is the new maximum connection capacity within the municipality until 2030"
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.gtlaw.com/en/insights/2024/3/challenges-in-the-dutch-data-center-market",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "the Dutch government has imposed new rules for hyperscale data centers, and the Municipality of Amsterdam has issued a preparatory decision restricting the development of new data center projects"
  },
  {
   "url": "https://zoek.officielebekendmakingen.nl/stcrt-2023-35432.html",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "deze instructieregels bepalen dat een omgevingsplan geen hyperscale datacentra toelaat"
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.dutchdatacenters.nl/en/nieuws/ten-years-of-state-of-the-dutch-data-centers-a-decade-of-growth-and-challenges/",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "While the Amsterdam Metropolitan Area (MRA) still accounts for approximately 70% of colocation capacity, growth is shifting toward regions such as Groningen, South Holland, and North Brabant"
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.telecompaper.com/news/dutch-data-centre-association-expects-record-eur-14-bln-investment-in-2025--1539451",
   "stance": "contradicts",
   "quote": "Almost EUR 1.4 billion should be invested in the construction and equipment of colocation data centres this year, a sharp increase from previous years"
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.stedin.net/over-stedin/pers-en-media/persberichten/ruimte-op-het-zeeuwse-stroomnet-voor-61-bedrijven",
   "stance": "contradicts",
   "quote": "Netbeheerders Stedin en TenneT kunnen naar verwachting 61 Zeeuwse bedrijven en instellingen de gevraagde ruimte geven op het stroomnet voor een nieuwe of zwaardere aansluiting"
  }
 ]
}

